reviews_data.review_text: It's a cozy place to hang out and grab a cup of coffee. The Oreo Cream Cheese and Pecan Croissant are my favorites, although I usually get my desserts to take away but this place is nice to stay and chat.

I clearly asked for a CHOCOLATE mousse, not a vanilla one. (I came 7/25/24 at 9:15am, if you want to tell the young guy with dark hair that took my order to get his ears checked). I absolutely hate vanilla. I tried it, and it tasted very fake, barely masking the hydrogenated soy bean oil in it. I tried a bit on the top, and it was so gross that I just threw it away. We ordered in, and my drink came in a to go cup, and my friend's came in an actual glass. There goes getting any actual cute photos. Make up your mind. My friend ordered a hot chocolate, which wasn't bad, albeit plain all things considered. My chai latte was gross. It had almost no spices in it, which is why I suspect they put a ton of cinnamon on top, to try and mask this. It basically just tasted of steamed milk, which is freaking gross. I live in a pretty small city, and there is WAY better chai lattes there than this place. Waste of money.  Also, do something about the ants on your patio that are eating your customers when they sit outside.
I tried the Napoleon cake, it was not bad. Definitely one time try

Always have a lovely experience at this shop. Super friendly and nice staff and always clean. Well decorated and light up for just a perfect start to your morning eating a macaroon while sipping on coffee. Enjoy and cheers!!
Greedy, avaricious owners charging $0.50 cents for tap water.

Why did your Cafe begin to charge for water? I am not going to pay extra for a 12 Oz cup of water especially as they used to have it available for free. Seems like they may have some management/financial issue behind the scenes‚Ä¶Sad that a respected restaurant would do this.
More expensive on their desserts than I usually pay....very good though
Pastries are so delicious
Amelie's is my favorite coffee shop and bakery in the area. Their espresso is really good. The macaroons are üî•. Don't sleep on the salted caramel brownies either.

The cappuccino and pastries were good.  However, there was a swarm of flies inside the glass where the sweets were located.  This was pointed out to an employee who responded ‚ÄúI know‚Äù.   We also noted the crescent rolls that were sitting out were combined with the fresh.  Seeing this was quite disappointing.

This is a nice little place around Pineville. If you are looking for coffee date or just wanted to try some good coffee and other French treats then this is the place for you. Baked Almond croissant was so good, you should not miss that. Macaroons were also delicious. This place has really nice inside and outside seating with good Atmosphere. Need to go back and try some more items. Overall 4.25/5 ‚≠êÔ∏è

20240528: Amelie's has wonderful pastries, coffee, and French bistro food. I like the macarons and coisants with cafe au lait.  For my birthday, Amelie's sent me a $5 birthday coupon, which covered most of the cost of this wonderful macaron and decaf coffee.
Horrible place the employees flirt with customers and sleep with married men Christopher is disgusting at this location don't take your men there
The food and sweets are great! Went there on a rainy day and the concrete floor was a bit slippery from the water. You order at the counter and they bring the food to your table.
Very nice people, great food, reasonable prices! Loved it

Update (5/10/24) to old review. I ordered one of my favorite desserts "Fresh Fruits Tart". I have had this tart many times, but today it was gravely different "water down, lighter color, and nasty taste." What happened to my favorite desserts!   See picture -- changes to a perfect dessert is never good!  Lower rating required for messing up my dessert.
Good coffee and  dessert.Too often there is a broken coffee machine and therefore no coffee .
The atmosphere takes you to a quaint little corner of France. The pastries are delightful and delicious.
Love the pastry here even though it is a bit pricey.  Wish there was one nearer to me.
The kid who delivered our food, his name is Joey. He was so pleasant & asked us what else we needed. In this day where service sucks everywhere it was was awesome to have a smiling face like Joey's
Great quality foods ,fresh,friendly staff. Atmosphere 100 %
There were multiple gnats in the display case and something fuzzy stuck to my eclair. I usually have no complaints with Amelie's but I'm a bit put off after today. Always a great atmosphere, though

One slice of roast beef and one be slice of cheese cold for $12, tomato soup has the worst taste, broccoli soup is all water, coffee tasted so old and just gross.  $30 for total garbage.  Service was delightful which was lovely.
The best service aver. The food is amazing I had Zahra took my order she is so professional and very knowledgeable and helpful.

The coffee was horrible. The person who makes it needs to know that it can't be so strong that we can't drink without diluting it with water. Unfortunately they didn't keep hot water but it was cold and we ended up with cold coffee.
Wonderful pastries and coffees! Great selection of other drinks, teas and food.
First time coming on a late evening and the hot chocolate and pastries were delicious! It wasn't too busy. Nicely decorated too.

My experience:  Ambience is pretty nice, service is great.  Food and drinks - not great.  1. I ordered light roast coffee - it's bitter than the dark roast.  2. Brownie tart(?) Is hard, I expected a brownie to be soft, but it was hard - but the representative helped me reace with the espresso one. It's tasty.  Eclair is nice.
Everything here is delicious ü§§ I've never ordered anything I didn't enjoy!
Not sure why this amelies location is charging $5 for lettuce, tomato and basic toppings that come on a sandwich, but these items cost almost the cost of the sandwich itself!
This place is awesome for a snack or meal anytime.
Inconsistent food, inconsistent service, decent pastries and baked goods. It's better than a Starbucks if you don't mind waiting an hour for pickup orders

The pastries and sandwiches might be a little bit on the expensive side but they are always delicious. Everything here looks great and tastes fantastic. It's a great place to meet a friend for coffee and a chat.

Interesting eclectic place. Polite service. Came in for macaroons but ended up with the caramel brownie torte. SO Good. Got a light roast coffee to cut the rich dessert...it was stronger than I was expecting but overall I enjoyed my visit
Such a cozy place to have a breakfast
